Seun Kuti, the youngest son of legendary Afrobeat singer, Fela Kuti, has alleged most rich people in Nigeria are into money rituals. The singer argued no African has ever made money without engaging in ritual killings. Taking to his Instagram page, Seun Kuti wrote: “Don’t do money rituals. Don’t kill people for money. Abeg which African rich man no dey kill people for money? “99 per cent of the wealth in the country is earned by sacrificing the lives and destinies of millions of Nigerians, that is the real money ritual!!   I’m not in a haste to win Grammy- Bella Shmurda     How to make it big acting, by Ini Edo     Actress Nkechi Blessing gets lands as birthday gift   - Advertisement - “Abi na ordinary eye building dey take collapse crush children to death for school? All the lives Wey bad roads dey take? All the avoidable deaths in our hospital? He added: “Listen NIGERIA ITSELF IS A MONEY RITUAL! And all your big men and women are RITUALISTS. “Abi na ordinary eye Hairdresser dey take turn Oil Mogul? Abeg make una shift. #getthesax.” SPONSORED